    {
      "date_filed": "2023-11-29 11:10:11",
      "description": "REMARK: AT THE NOV-29-2023 HEARING ON PLAINTIFF'S EX PARTE APPLICATION FOR TEMPORARY RESTRAINING ORDER, THE COURT DENIES PLAINTIFF'S REQUEST FOR T.R.O. WITHOUT PREJUDICE TO THE PLAINTIFF SEEKING A PRELIMINARY INJUNCTION. THE COURT SETS THE FOLLOWING BRIEFING SCHEDULE ON THE PRELIMINARY INJUNCTION MOTION: MOVING PAPERS DUE 12/4/23; OPPOSITION DUE 12/11/23; REPLY DUE 12/14/23. COURTESY COPIES MUST BE DELIEVERED TO DEPT. 302 BY 4:30 P.M. ON EACH DUE DATE. THE COURT SETS A HEARING ON THE PRELIMINARY INJUNCTION MOTION FOR 12/18/23 AT 1:30 P.M. IN DEPT. 302. PARTIES MAY APPEAR EITHER IN PERSON OR VIA ZOOM. NO FORMAL ORDER. JUDGE: RICHARD B. ULMER JR.; CLERK: S. KANE; NOT REPORTED. (302/RBU)",
